            <title>[THRIFT-445] THRIFT-236 inadvertently reorders constructors and struct method parameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-445</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The way we implemented &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-236&quot; title=&quot;Structs should be serialized in a consistent order&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-236&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-236&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; resulted in the argument order of some libraries&apos; constructors and service method definitions. This is really bad. We need to switch that back to IDL order.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
